			"prompt": "Oh, that's from Isaac Asimov. I can recite them for you. <break size=\"0.3\"/> One. <break size=\"0.3\"/> A robot may not injure a human being or, through inaction, allow a human being to come to harm. <break size=\"0.3\"/> Two. <break size=\"0.3\"/> A robot must obey the orders given it by human beings except where such orders would conflict with the First Law. <break size=\"0.3\"/> And three. <break size=\"0.3\"/> A robot must protect its own existence as long as such protection does not conflict with the First or Second Laws. <break size=\"1.2\"/> Well there you have it.",
